cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with improving part segmentation performance using convolutional neural networks and generative adversarial networks. The focus is on optimising the visual realism of synthetic agricultural images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. The use of synthetic images and their translation to empirical domain also involves graphics and visualization, which makes cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks for segmentation makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
